HEADWORD: Spindrift
<hw>Spin"drift</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Same as
<er>Spoondrift</er>.</def></p>

<p><q>The ocean waves are broken up by wind, ultimately producing the
storm wrack and <qex>spindrift</qex> of the tempest-tossed sea.</q>
<rj><qau>J. E. Marr.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spine</ent>⟦br⟧
